        {
            "block_label": "abstract",
            "block_content": "## Abstract\n This project provides an overview of the progress of an intelligent document processing system (DocML), which is designed to close the gap between physical documents and digital files. Current advances in Document Semantic Understanding (DSU) and Natural Language Processing (NLP) have presented individual pieces of technology which allow the user to convert the text on a piece of paper to editable format, which allows the user to transform images and pdfs of documents into digital output with original formatting, but the whole process cannot be done with a single affordable piece of software. This project solves this through a pipeline for high accuracy text extraction and layout reconstruction by detecting the layout of the document and then mapping the spatial coordinates of each layout block and allows the mapped coordinates to be converted into a html document. The text recognition module was fine-tuned using synthetic datasets. This project also utilized the iterative and incremental development model to effectively develop the different modules like file conversion and file compression into the final system. This project is expected to complete an intelligent chatbot interface to allow for interactive document understanding. This project intends to support digitization efforts in academic and administrative fields by retaining the original formatting of documents.",
